nodes.bodyText:
I agree that assigning null should be avoided. But sometimes it cannot be, many java library methods return null and use it. For this case, I have converted it to be an Optional, it will look like :

currentProcessStatus = Optional.empty();
currentJobId = Optional.empty();

With these changes the readability of the code elsewhere gets affected (gets better for one and not so much for other I think), specially with currentProcessStatus (as it is a Future). But this does not prevent programmer from doing a check, they now have to do a isPresent() check or variation of that. Although with Optional it may be more intuitive. Also optional comes with space and time overhead - https://homes.cs.washington.edu/~mernst/advice/nothing-is-better-than-optional.html#overhead
I will continue thinking of better way, let me know what you think of this and if you have any other suggestion.

